=======================

## Calendar: roster-highlighted days (light blue)
- frontend/src/pages/RosterView/CalendarGrid.tsx
  Added `rosterDates: Set<string>` prop and `onMonthChange` callback.
  Days with rosters render with `bg-blue-100`.

- frontend/src/pages/RosterView/index.tsx
  Added `rosterDates` state and `handleMonthChange` that fetches dates
  for the visible month via `rosterApi.getRosterDatesInRange`.

- frontend/src/api/roster.ts
  Added `getRosterDatesInRange(from, to)` → `Set<string>`.

## Split slot generation from 12h → 6h blocks
- backend/src/services/scheduling/generator.ts
  Replaced DAY_SHIFT/NIGHT_SHIFT constants with SHIFT_BLOCKS array
  (4 × 6-hour blocks: 00:00–06:00, 06:00–12:00, 12:00–18:00, 18:00–00:00).
  Generation loop now iterates over all 4 blocks instead of 2 shifts.
  Block 3 (18:00–00:00) uses end_time "00:00:00" — filter helpers handle the
  midnight crossing correctly (isOvernight, shiftDurationMinutes, etc.).

## Part-timer daily cap (6h)
- backend/src/services/scheduling/filter.ts
  Added Step 0 (part-time max-hours) to the pipeline header comment.
  Added pure-field check in evaluateCandidate: part_time + slotDuration > 360
  → hard block with "Part-time staff cannot work shifts exceeding 6 hours".
  Placed before Step 1 (availability check) to avoid unnecessary DB queries.

  Modified Step 3 (daily hours check) to use per-employment-type limit:
  part_time → 360 min cap, full_time → 720 min cap. This prevents part-timers
  from being assigned to multiple 6h blocks in one day.

## 00:00–06:00 column empty in CrewGrid (overnight wrap)
- frontend/src/pages/RosterView/CrewGrid.tsx
  Added `isOvernightShift()` and `slotsForBlock()` — for block 0, includes
  overnight slots that started at block 3 (18:00) and wrap around.
  Overnight-wrap cells forced to span 1 instead of trying to span back to
  block 3.

